4bda444e-028c-48e3-967d-b6788f32aab9.39a94160-745f-4c9e-8db2-032ce53c2ed2.description=
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The directory to check.
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - The number of children.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success - The operation succeeded.

4bda444e-028c-48e3-967d-b6788f32aab9.85a810df-4894-407c-a920-a6b2352f5b39.description=
Copies a file or directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The file or directory to copy.
destination - the location to copy the file or directory to.
removeSource - Specifies whether the source should be removed if the copy operation is successful (true, false).
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host during this operation.
password - The password for the user.
overwrite - If false the operation will fail if Destination exists.

Responses\:
success - Was able to copy file/directory.
failure - Unable to copy file/directory.

Note\:
This copy operation is modeled after the Windows command-line copy operation.  So given a sample directory structure\:
--DirectoryA
   |--File1
   |--File2
   |--DirectoryC
       |-File5

--DirectoryB
   |--File3
   |--File4

If your Source is "DirectoryA" and your Destination is "DirectoryB" your end result will be\:
--DirectoryA
   |--File1
   |--File2
   |--DirectoryC
       |-File5

--DirectoryB
   |--File3
   |--File4
   |--File1
   |--File2
   |--DirectoryC
       |-File5

4bda444e-028c-48e3-967d-b6788f32aab9.9a63292a-8cef-4278-9589-aa7db8a85dd2.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

4bda444e-028c-48e3-967d-b6788f32aab9.a40fa032-53d8-41ca-a048-1a4688eb19dc.description=
FSRename changes the name of a file.  This operation will not move a file to a different directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The file to rename, including directory.
newName - The new name of the file, NOT INCLUDING DIRECTORY.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host for this operation.
password - Password for the user.
overwrite - If false the operation will fail if newName exists (true, false).

Responses\:
failure - The rename failed.
success - The rename succeeded.

4bda444e-028c-48e3-967d-b6788f32aab9.c9b830f4-0047-475b-9a56-0fe73409b45a.description=
Checks to see if a list contains every element in another list.

Inputs\:
sublist -The contained list.
container - The containing list.
delimiter - A delimiter separating elements in the two lists. Default is a comma
ignoreCase - If set to 'True' then the compare is not case sensitive. Default is True

Responses\:
true - sublist is contained in container.
false - sublist is not contained in container.

Results\:
Result - All items contained in the sublist that are not in the container.
